{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {META_DATA}: HOW TO TRAIN YOUR DRAGON
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {META_DATA}: Written by
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {META_DATA}: Dean DeBlois & Chris Sanders
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {META_DATA}: Final Draft February 13, 2010
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NORTH SEA/VILLAGE - NIGHT
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We skim above a dark, wild ocean.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera turns toward a lone island, Berk.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a gigantic shard of rock jutting straight out of the water.
{0:0:0 - 0:0:36} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{0:0:34 - 0:0:36} {DIALOGUE}: This, is Berk.
{0:0:36 - 0:0:41} {DIALOGUE}: It's twelve days North of hopeless, and a few degrees South of freezing to death.
{0:0:41 - 0:0:45} {DIALOGUE}: It's located solidly on the meridian of misery.
{0:0:41 - 0:0:49} {DIALOGUE}: The camera drifts over rolling hills to reveal a small village nestled on an outcropping of sea mounts.
{0:0:41 - 0:0:49} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{0:0:46 - 0:0:49} {DIALOGUE}: My village.
{0:0:46 - 0:0:49} {DIALOGUE}: In a word, sturdy.
{0:0:49 - 0:0:54} {DIALOGUE}: And it's been here for seven generations, but every single building is new.
{0:0:49 - 0:0:58} {DIALOGUE}: The camera drifts closer, circling.
{0:0:49 - 0:0:58} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{0:0:54 - 0:0:58} {DIALOGUE}: We have fishing, hunting, and a charming view of the sunsets.
{0:0:59 - 0:1:2} {DIALOGUE}: The only problems are the pests.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:6} {DIALOGUE}: You see, most places have mice or mosquitos.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {DIALOGUE}: We have... Sheep graze peacefully on a hillside.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {DIALOGUE}: Suddenly one is snatched.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STOICK'S HOUSE - CONTINUOUS
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A door is pulled open... as a DRAGON swoops directly toward it, BLASTING FIRE.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door is SLAMMED.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fire shoots through the slats of wood, illuminating HICCUP, a gangly teenage Viking.
{0:1:3 - 0:1:13} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{0:1:11 - 0:1:13} {DIALOGUE}: ...dragons.
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STOICK'S HOUSE
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reopens the sizzling door, as leaps off of the front porch.
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He weaves through the erupting mayhem as Vikings pour out of the buildings, ready for a fight.
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 2.
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More dragons swarm in, setting rooftops alight and hauling off sheep.
{0:1:11 - 0:1:16} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{0:1:14 - 0:1:16} {DIALOGUE}: Most people would leave.
{0:1:14 - 0:1:16} {DIALOGUE}: Not us.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:20} {DIALOGUE}: We're Vikings.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:20} {DIALOGUE}: We have stubbornness issues.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:23} {DIALOGUE}: Vikings sound the alarm.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:23} {DIALOGUE}: Viking men and women pour out into the streets, axes in hand.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:23} {DIALOGUE}: ON HICCUP darting through alleys, staying under eaves, making his way through the battle.
{0:1:16 - 0:1:23} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{0:1:22 - 0:1:23} {DIALOGUE}: My name's Hiccup.
{0:1:24 - 0:1:27} {DIALOGUE}: Great name, I know.
{0:1:24 - 0:1:27} {DIALOGUE}: But it's not the worst.
{0:1:27 - 0:1:31} {DIALOGUE}: Parents believe a hideous name will frighten off gnomes and trolls.
{0:1:31 - 0:1:33} {DIALOGUE}: Like our charming Viking demeanor wouldn't do that.
{0:1:31 - 0:1:49} {DIALOGUE}: Dragons sweep back and forth, dodging axes and blasting the Vikings who throw them.
{0:1:31 - 0:1:49} {DIALOGUE}: A burly warrior gets tossed in an explosion, knocking Hiccup to the ground.
