{0:4:18 - 0:4:20} {DIALOGUE}: Because killing a dragon is everything around here.
{0:4:18 - 0:4:24} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - LOWER PLAINS - CONTINUOUS
{0:4:18 - 0:4:24} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nadders land, gathering like seagulls around a seemingly vacant house.
{0:4:18 - 0:4:24} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{0:4:21 - 0:4:24} {DIALOGUE}: A Nadder head is sure to get me at least noticed.
{0:4:21 - 0:4:26} {DIALOGUE}: The Nadders clamber onto the building, tearing the roof and walls apart.
{0:4:21 - 0:4:26} {DIALOGUE}: Sheep pour out and SCATTER.
{0:4:21 - 0:4:26} {DIALOGUE}: Elsewhere, hippo-like Gronckles pick drying racks clean of fish and fly off like loaded pelicans.
{0:4:21 - 0:4:26} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{0:4:24 - 0:4:26} {DIALOGUE}: Gronckles are tough.
{0:4:26 - 0:4:29} {DIALOGUE}: Taking down one of those would definitely get me a girlfriend.
{0:4:26 - 0:4:35} {DIALOGUE}: A stealthy, snake-like dragon head peeks over a rooftop, breathing gas into a chimney.
