{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Just... let me... why don't you... The Nadder spins around and races back toward them like a Raptor.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Astrid untangles herself and tries to pull her axe from Hiccup's shield... which is attached to his limp, gangly arm.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: She PLANTS her foot on his torso and YANKS the axe free, still burrowed into the shield.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 37.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She SPINS and SWINGS the axe and shield, scoring a DIRECT HIT on the oncoming Nadder's NOSE.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It yelps and scurries off.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Well done, Astrid.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Gobber hobbles off to wrestle the Nadder back into his cave.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup gets to his feet -- all eyes are upon him.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: He turns to find Astrid glaring at him, winded.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: ASTRID
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Is this some kind of a joke to you?
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Our parents' war is about to become ours.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Figure out which side you're on.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: She grabs her axe and stomps off.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup watches, stung.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COVE - MAGIC HOUR
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: CLOSE ON
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: A fish... being thrown into the cove.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: It hits the ground and slides.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: A moment later, Hiccup peeks through a gap in the rock, looking around cautiously.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Nothing.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup squeezes through and enters the cove.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: A BEAT, then Hiccup hears a SNORT from behind him.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup turns to see the Night Fury, crouched on a rock like a stealthy panther.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: It descends, approaching him... ready to pounce.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup swallows his fear and offers the fish.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Doing so reveals the dagger at his waist.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: The dragon sees it and hisses.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup reaches for it, eliciting a growl.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: He pauses, carefully lifts it by the handle, and tosses it away.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: The dragon calms.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {DIALOGUE}: As it approaches the fish, Hiccup notices that it's missing teeth.
{0:26:10 - 0:29:1} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
