{0:29:6 - 0:29:16} {DIALOGUE}: Uh, no.
{0:29:15 - 0:29:16} {DIALOGUE}: No, I don't have any more.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: The Fury backs Hiccup against a rock, placing himself the same position as before.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: The dragon closes in over him, staring blankly.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: A tense moment passes... then Toothless regurgitates a chunk of fish onto Hiccup's lap.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: They exchange stares.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup realizes what Toothless wants him to do.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup crouches slowly and squeamishly picks it up.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: The dragon waits expectantly.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup gags and gnaws off a bite of the slimy fish.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: He forces a smile.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless mimics him.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Amazed, Hiccup sits up and tries to touch him.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless HISSES and flaps off to a crash on the other side of the cove.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: He BLASTS the mossy ground to a red-hot temperature... and curls up on it like a giant dog.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: He turns to find Hiccup seated beside him.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless tolerates his persistent presence... until Hiccup tries to touch his damaged tail.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless SNAPS at him.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup takes the hint and leaves.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COVE - LATER
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's MAGIC HOUR.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless wakes, hanging upside down from a tree.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spots Hiccup sitting on the other side of the cove.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketching in the sand.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON a sketch of Toothless.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup draws with a stick, minding his own business.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless appears behind him, watching carefully.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aware of his presence, Hiccup continues, trying not to scare him off.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless walks off.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later, he reappears with an entire sapling, drawing lines in the sand.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rushes here and there, making haphazard lines in every direction.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, Toothless drops the tree and inspects his work.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seems pleased.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 39.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup stands and takes in the sprawling scribble, amazed by it.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He accidentally steps onto one of the lines, eliciting an instant growl from Toothless.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps on it again.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless growls again.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Realizing how sensitive he is, Hiccup steps carefully between each line, turning round and round until he unwittingly bumps into Toothless.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless snorts.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Once again, they're face to face.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup slowly extends his hand.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless hesitates.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup turns his head away and closes his eyes.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To his amazement, Toothless bridges the gap and presses his muzzle against Hiccup's hand.
{0:29:15 - 0:33:17} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a flash, the dragon is gone, leaving Hiccup astounded.
