{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick staggers on the steps, breaking inside.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DOCKS/OPEN SEA - DAY
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Broken-down catapults and trebuchets are bundled up and lowered from the cliffs.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Below on the docks, Vikings load the heavy artillery into the hulls of awaiting ships.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Children and the elderly gather to on the walkways to wave apprehensive farewells to the departing warriors.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lastly, Toothless is loaded aboard Stoick's ship, chained down to a palette, muzzled, and restrained with a weighty neck ring.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks exhausted, miserable.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 79.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick crosses to the bow as the ship pushes off and joins the amassed armada of ships adrift in the harbor.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick's brow is furrowed, all warmth drained away.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns west and glares at the horizon with cold determination.
{1:6:18 - 1:7:16} {CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{1:7:15 - 1:7:16} {DIALOGUE}: Set sail!
{1:7:17 - 1:7:19} {DIALOGUE}: We head for Helheim's Gate.
{1:7:17 - 1:7:30} {DIALOGUE}: He then notices HICCUP watching from his familiar cliff-side perch beyond the village.
{1:7:17 - 1:7:30} {DIALOGUE}: Their eyes meet, full of hurt and regret.
{1:7:17 - 1:7:30} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup slowly shakes his head in warning.
{1:7:17 - 1:7:30} {DIALOGUE}: Stoick breaks the stare and turns to Toothless, fuming.
