{1:25:44 - 1:25:46} {DIALOGUE}: I'm happy to see you too, bud.
{1:25:44 - 1:25:52} {DIALOGUE}: Now just-- Toothless steps on his groin, causing Hiccup to sit BOLT UPRIGHT with a YELP.
{1:25:44 - 1:25:52} {DIALOGUE}: He looks around, confounded.
{1:25:44 - 1:25:52} {DIALOGUE}: He's in his bed, moved beside the fire pit on the main floor of his house.
{1:25:44 - 1:25:52} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:25:49 - 1:25:52} {DIALOGUE}: I'm in my house.
{1:25:49 - 1:25:55} {META_DATA}: (re: Toothless, leaning over him, excited)
{1:25:53 - 1:25:55} {DIALOGUE}: You're in my house.
{1:25:53 - 1:25:57} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless TEARS around the room, knocking things over, far too big for the space.
{1:25:53 - 1:25:57} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:25:55 - 1:25:57} {DIALOGUE}: Uh...does my dad know you're in here?!
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless pauses at the foot of the bed, tongue wagging.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: He eyes the rafters... and LEAPS UP onto them, brimming with 'happy dog' energy.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {META_DATA}: (DISTRESSED)
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Okay, okay -- no Toothless!
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Aw, come on... Hiccup shifts to get out of bed... then pauses... sensing that something is wrong.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: He peels back the covers slowly.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: What he sees startles, horrifies, and overwhelms him -- all at once.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 102.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE BARE FLOOR His booted foot touches down.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Followed by a mechanical prosthetic in place of his second leg.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's an ingenious spring-loaded replacement, made of wood and iron.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless lands by the bed and approaches calmly, sniffing the new leg.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his eyes to meet Hiccup's, seemingly aware of what Hiccup is going through.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup braces himself on the bedpost and tries to stand on it.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He winces and stifles the pain...
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Okay...okay... ... but STUMBLES with the first step.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless catches Hiccup's fall with his head... and slowly lifts him up, stabilizing him.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Thanks bud.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup leans on him like a crutch.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: They take a few steps together.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Their missing parts form a poetic silhouette as they make their way toward the door.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup pries it open (as he did in the opening scene), revealing a MONSTROUS NIGHTMARE flapping outside the door.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup YELPS and slams the door closed.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: He turns to Toothless, alarmed.
{1:25:55 - 1:26:2} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{1:26:0 - 1:26:2} {DIALOGUE}: Toothless?
{1:26:0 - 1:27:0} {DIALOGUE}: Stay here, bud.
{1:26:0 - 1:27:0} {DIALOGUE}: Hiccup pauses... and cracks the door open again.
{1:26:0 - 1:27:0} {DIALOGUE}: He peeks outside, his eyes widening.
{1:26:0 - 1:27:0} {DIALOGUE}: He allows to door to swing open, revealing... ... the Monstrous Nightmare, carrying Snotlout on its back.
{1:26:0 - 1:27:0} {CHARACTER_NAME}: SNOTLOUT
{1:26:56 - 1:27:0} {DIALOGUE}: Come on guys, get ready!
{1:27:0 - 1:27:1} {DIALOGUE}: Hold on tight!
{1:27:0 - 1:27:1} {DIALOGUE}: Here we go!
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {DIALOGUE}: A class of newbie dragon riders follow him through frame on a variety of dragons, pulling back the curtain on an amazing vista in which:
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 103.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vikings and dragons mill about by the dozen, basking on the rooftops, weaving along the plaza.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one seems upset, there isn't a sword in sight.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Under the framework of a MASSIVE BARN, a Nadder BLASTS fire onto a metal brace.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It steps back to let a Viking hammer it into shape.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nearby, a Gronkle lands, carrying a tree trunk in his mouth.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shows a Viking what he's found.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Viking pats his head.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another Viking backs a Zippleback into a stall to check it for size.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup takes a step outside, finding Stoick waiting for him on the step.
{1:27:0 - 1:27:16} {CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{1:27:14 - 1:27:16} {DIALOGUE}: I knew it.
{1:27:14 - 1:27:16} {DIALOGUE}: I'm dead.
{1:27:14 - 1:27:21} {DIALOGUE}: Stoick laughs.
{1:27:14 - 1:27:21} {CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{1:27:17 - 1:27:21} {DIALOGUE}: No, but you gave it your best shot.
{1:27:17 - 1:27:21} {DIALOGUE}: He puts his arm around Hiccup, steadying him.
{1:27:17 - 1:27:21} {DIALOGUE}: He gestures to the transformed village.
{1:27:17 - 1:27:21} {CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
